1
00:00:05,930 --> 00:00:09,040
Kṛṣṇa is not alone.

2
00:00:09,040 --> 00:00:13,250
Kṛṣṇa does not live in isolation
or in a vacuum.

3
00:00:13,390 --> 00:00:16,130
[Vacuum? Krishna Is not Alone]

4
00:00:16,160 --> 00:00:24,810
And it’s not a full conception of Kṛṣṇa—
to conceive of Him alone.

5
00:00:24,810 --> 00:00:26,890
Sometimes Guru Mahārāj
will say,

6
00:00:26,890 --> 00:00:29,370
“In the famous Gita śloka:

7
00:00:29,370 --> 00:00:33,060
bahūnāṁ janmanām ante
jñānavān māṁ prapadyate

8
00:00:33,060 --> 00:00:38,810
vāsudevaḥ sarvam iti
sa mahātmā su-durlabhaḥ
[Bg: 7.19]

9
00:00:38,810 --> 00:00:43,676
it is saying,
‘After many, many births

10
00:00:43,676 --> 00:00:50,053
a rare mahātmā may come along
who realizes: vāsudevaḥ sarvam iti—

11
00:00:50,053 --> 00:00:53,833
Kṛṣṇa is everything,
He is the source of everything;

12
00:00:53,833 --> 00:00:57,144
everything comes from Kṛṣṇa,
and Kṛṣṇa is everything.’”

13
00:00:57,144 --> 00:00:58,482
But Guru Mahārāj said,

14
00:00:58,482 --> 00:01:02,845
“That’s the beginning
of the first personal conception

15
00:01:02,845 --> 00:01:10,205
in the Brahman world, the Brahmā world,
first personal conception,

16
00:01:10,205 --> 00:01:22,363
but where is His potency,
His counterpart, His sweet self?”

17
00:01:23,017 --> 00:01:28,487
So, Guru Mahārāj would say,
“Conceiving of Kṛṣṇa alone,

18
00:01:28,487 --> 00:01:30,895
as implied in this śloka,

19
00:01:30,895 --> 00:01:36,955
means Kṛṣṇa conception
at a distance.”

20
00:01:36,955 --> 00:01:42,909
Sometimes we hear 
of Mirabai in India.

21
00:01:42,909 --> 00:01:46,001
Everyone in India 
is enamoured by Mirabai,

22
00:01:46,001 --> 00:01:50,434
“She is such a great devotee 
and devoted from her childhood,

23
00:01:50,434 --> 00:01:55,856
and writing so many songs
mad with praise of Kṛṣṇa.”

24
00:01:56,686 --> 00:01:58,753
But Śrīla Guru Mahārāj
will point out

25
00:01:58,753 --> 00:02:02,383
for the sake of analysis 
and our benefit—

26
00:02:02,383 --> 00:02:05,213
we need to understand
progressive theism—

27
00:02:05,213 --> 00:02:10,243
he would say, “Well, Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur, 
Saraswatī Ṭhākur and those in their line

28
00:02:10,243 --> 00:02:15,627
do not recognise her 
as a substantial devotee of Kṛṣṇa.

29
00:02:15,627 --> 00:02:20,047
Not saying ‘not a devotee of Kṛṣṇa’,
but as a substantial devotee of Kṛṣṇa.”

30
00:02:20,047 --> 00:02:22,228
And people say, “Why?

31
00:02:22,228 --> 00:02:26,146
Her songs are full 
of mad praise of Kṛṣṇa.

32
00:02:26,146 --> 00:02:28,366
So many songs: 
Mira and Kṛṣṇa.

33
00:02:28,366 --> 00:02:31,826
She is always writing songs 
about Mira and Kṛṣṇa.”

34
00:02:31,826 --> 00:02:35,752
And that’s the point:
her and Kṛṣṇa.

35
00:02:35,752 --> 00:02:42,000
Not the āśraya-vigraha, not Rādhārāṇī, 
not Lalitā–Viśākhā,

36
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:46,720
not Rūpa–Rati,
but Mira and Kṛṣṇa.

37
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:53,243
So, in as much as those,
who are near and dear to Kṛṣṇa

38
00:02:53,243 --> 00:03:00,413
have been bypassed 
or eliminated, or not recognized

39
00:03:00,413 --> 00:03:04,953
by the ontological 
method of measurement

40
00:03:04,953 --> 00:03:09,600
it means this is a distant 
Kṛṣṇa conception

41
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:13,840
for where can Kṛṣṇa be seen alone, 
but at a great distance,

42
00:03:13,840 --> 00:03:16,470
far from the Absolute centre;

43
00:03:16,470 --> 00:03:22,220
not the extreme, 
not the golden mean.

44
00:03:22,220 --> 00:03:27,041
‘Golden mean’ means
the aprākṛta‒līla of Kṛṣṇa—

45
00:03:27,041 --> 00:03:29,538
Goloka Vṛndāvan, where 
there is Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa,

46
00:03:29,538 --> 00:03:34,095
Lalitā–Viśākhā, Rupa–Rati,
Subal–Sridam,

47
00:03:34,095 --> 00:03:38,575
Nanda–Yaśodā, gopa–gopī,
etc.

48
00:03:38,575 --> 00:03:43,366
So, Kṛṣṇa is worshipped
along with His paraphernalia—

49
00:03:43,366 --> 00:03:45,345
those who are dear to Kṛṣṇa.

